# License for the Comics Processing Framework

## 1. Code and Framework License (GPLv3)
The source code and framework provided in this repository are licensed under the **GNU General Public License v3.0 (GPLv3)**.

### Summary of GPLv3:
- You are free to **use, modify, and distribute** this software.
- Any modifications **must be released under the same GPLv3 license**.
- You **cannot** make proprietary versions based on this software.
- Provides **patent protection** against claims from contributors.

A copy of the full GPLv3 license can be found here:  
https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0.en.html

## 2. Trained Model License (CC BY-NC-SA 4.0)
The trained models shared in the external **[Drive folder]** are released under the **Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike 4.0 International (CC BY-NC-SA 4.0)** license.

### Summary of CC BY-NC-SA 4.0:
- You are free to **use, modify, and redistribute** the trained models.
- **NonCommercial**: You may not use the models for commercial purposes.
- **ShareAlike**: If you modify or build upon the models, you must distribute your new models under the same license.

Full details can be found at:  
https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/

## 3. Dataset Handling and Manga109 Limitations
The framework allows users to process **existing datasets and their own datasets** but does not redistribute copyrighted datasets. As such, all the datasets used **are not included in this repository**.

### Manga109-Specific Restrictions:
- The **Manga109 dataset** (https://www.manga109.org/en/) is used in training some of the weights (specifically, the one with the suffix "-m109" in their name).
- The **Manga109 dataset is restricted to academic use only**.
- Users are responsible for ensuring compliance with **Manga109's license** if they choose to use it, or to use the weights trained on it.

